WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-US

00:00:02.233 --> 00:00:04.066
When it comes to functional skin care

00:00:04.066 --> 00:00:05.200
and ingredient-oriented skin care,

00:00:05.200 --> 00:00:07.833
there is one brand we cannot avoid,

00:00:07.833 --> 00:00:09.733
and that is Paula's Choice.

00:00:09.833 --> 00:00:10.800
Paula's Choice

00:00:10.800 --> 00:00:13.233
was established earlier

00:00:13.233 --> 00:00:14.866
than the ingredient-oriented brands we are familiar with

00:00:14.866 --> 00:00:16.200
, such as SkinCeuticals

00:00:16.200 --> 00:00:18.800
and The Ordinary.

00:00:18.933 --> 00:00:21.300
Some people call it the originator of acid peeling,

00:00:21.300 --> 00:00:24.700
while others call it the granddaughter of functional ingredient-oriented brands.

00:00:24.700 --> 00:00:26.666
Hi everyone, I'm the formulator Xingxing.

00:00:26.666 --> 00:00:28.866
Today, I'll give you an inventory of

00:00:28.866 --> 00:00:31.900
dozens of products from the eight series of the Paula's Choice brand

00:00:31.900 --> 00:00:33.033
and show you

00:00:33.033 --> 00:00:34.500
which

00:00:34.500 --> 00:00:36.400
of their products

00:00:36.400 --> 00:00:39.300
are both scientific and reliable

00:00:39.300 --> 00:00:40.500
, and which have

00:00:40.500 --> 00:00:42.500
similar formulas and are not easy to use.

00:00:49.133 --> 00:00:51.100
If we want to talk about Paula's Choice,

00:00:51.100 --> 00:00:52.833
we must first understand

00:00:52.833 --> 00:00:54.433
what style

00:00:54.433 --> 00:00:55.900
and type of brand it is

00:00:55.933 --> 00:00:57.400
. Does it tell stories,

00:00:57.400 --> 00:00:58.200
talk about fashion

00:00:58.200 --> 00:01:00.600
, or focus on ingredients and science?

00:01:00.600 --> 00:01:03.933
Then we must start with

00:01:03.933 --> 00:01:05.800
its founder, Paula Pegan.

00:01:05.800 --> 00:01:06.633
Paula Pegan

00:01:06.633 --> 00:01:09.833
was born in Chicago in the 1950s. It is said that she

00:01:09.833 --> 00:01:11.600
suffered from eczema and acne

00:01:11.600 --> 00:01:14.133
in her childhood.

00:01:14.133 --> 00:01:16.700
, and she developed a strong interest in skincare.

00:01:16.700 --> 00:01:18.000
In her twenties,

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:19.633
she found a job at a department store

00:01:19.633 --> 00:01:22.433
as a salesperson at a cosmetics counter

00:01:22.433 --> 00:01:23.533
. However

00:01:23.600 --> 00:01:25.133
, she was fired

00:01:25.133 --> 00:01:27.333
after a few years

00:01:27.333 --> 00:01:29.533
because she told customers the truth

00:01:29.533 --> 00:01:31.733
about bad ingredients

00:01:31.733 --> 00:01:33.066
and products that could not be used.

00:01:33.200 --> 00:01:35.433
Being fired did not dampen

00:01:35.433 --> 00:01:39.000
her passion for skincare and ingredient research,

00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:40.700
so in the 1980s,

00:01:40.700 --> 00:01:43.833
she self-published her first book

00:01:43.833 --> 00:01:46.733
, "Blue Eyeshadow Should Be Banned.

00:01:46.733 --> 00:01:47.600
" The book

00:01:47.600 --> 00:01:50.333
satirized

00:01:50.333 --> 00:01:51.266
the phenomenon of

00:01:51.266 --> 00:01:53.800
following the makeup and skincare trends

00:01:53.800 --> 00:01:57.400
that were not suitable for individuals . In that era of storytelling, fashion, and trends,

00:01:57.400 --> 00:02:00.133
Paula was considered quite unique.

00:02:00.133 --> 00:02:01.500
In the early 1990s,

00:02:01.500 --> 00:02:04.066
Paula published her famous book, "

00:02:04.066 --> 00:02:07.600
Don't go to the Cosmetics counter without me

00:02:07.600 --> 00:02:10.000
," which meant that you must read this book

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:12.200
before going to the cosmetics counter.

00:02:12.200 --> 00:02:13.033
The book

00:02:13.033 --> 00:02:15.000
was republished several times.

00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:16.233
At the time, it seemed

00:02:16.233 --> 00:02:18.133
that no one

00:02:18.133 --> 00:02:21.000
could conduct such a large-scale cosmetics review

00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:22.633
, and this book

00:02:22.633 --> 00:02:25.633
also earned her

00:02:25.633 --> 00:02:28.533
the nickname "Cosmetics Cop," or "Cosmetics Police."

00:02:28.633 --> 00:02:30.100
In 1995,

00:02:30.100 --> 00:02:32.333
in response to the response from her fans,

00:02:32.400 --> 00:02:34.266
she founded her own brand

00:02:34.266 --> 00:02:36.300
, Paula's The brand

00:02:36.300 --> 00:02:37.266
Choice

00:02:37.266 --> 00:02:38.133
Paula's Choice

00:02:38.133 --> 00:02:39.133
advocated

00:02:39.133 --> 00:02:42.300
science-based and transparent ingredients,

00:02:42.300 --> 00:02:45.900
which was very avant-garde in the eyes of cosmetics at the time.

00:02:45.900 --> 00:02:47.333
It also

00:02:47.333 --> 00:02:50.333
laid a good foundation for various functional skin care brands

00:02:50.333 --> 00:02:52.100
that emerged later

00:02:52.133 --> 00:02:52.800
. Later,

00:02:52.800 --> 00:02:55.000
Paula's Choice can be said to be popular all over the world.

00:02:55.000 --> 00:02:56.633
In 2021,

00:02:56.633 --> 00:02:58.433
Paula's Choice was acquired by Unilever

00:02:58.433 --> 00:03:01.300
for 2.1 billion US dollars.

00:03:01.300 --> 00:03:04.033
Since then, it has further expanded its internationalization

00:03:04.033 --> 00:03:07.300
and has become a representative brand of rational skin care today.

00:03:07.300 --> 00:03:08.400
In summary,

00:03:08.400 --> 00:03:11.866
the brand Paula's Choice is a

00:03:11.900 --> 00:03:15.133
brand that does not tell stories but only talks about ingredients and science.

00:03:16.933 --> 00:03:18.033
After talking about the founder,

00:03:18.033 --> 00:03:19.200
let's talk about

00:03:19.200 --> 00:03:21.900
the 8 product series of Paula's Choice.

00:03:21.900 --> 00:03:23.500
Our common skin care products

00:03:23.500 --> 00:03:27.033
have two types of series divisions. Either they

00:03:27.033 --> 00:03:29.400
are divided according to skin type

00:03:29.400 --> 00:03:32.000
or they are divided according to efficacy.

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:34.000
However, Paula's Choice's series division

00:03:34.000 --> 00:03:36.200
is neither of these two methods.

00:03:36.266 --> 00:03:40.266
It is divided according to the intensity of your needs.

00:03:40.266 --> 00:03:42.500
Let me explain to you what demand intensity

00:03:42.500 --> 00:03:44.533
is. It means that when your skin

00:03:44.533 --> 00:03:47.033
becomes almost pathological,

00:03:47.033 --> 00:03:48.700
This kind of pores are particularly large,

00:03:48.700 --> 00:03:49.800
there are a lot of acne

00:03:49.800 --> 00:03:51.900
, and you are also experiencing a cliff-like aging.

00:03:51.900 --> 00:03:53.833
Your face is sagging .

00:03:53.833 --> 00:03:54.933
When you are in this state,

00:03:54.933 --> 00:03:58.033
it is called super-effectiveness demand.

00:03:58.033 --> 00:03:59.866
In the brand Paula's Choice,

00:03:59.866 --> 00:04:01.866
it corresponds to two series,

00:04:01.866 --> 00:04:03.266
one is clinical and the

00:04:03.266 --> 00:04:04.500
other is booster.

00:04:04.533 --> 00:04:06.600
Then there is another type, my skin

00:04:06.600 --> 00:04:07.466
is fine,

00:04:07.466 --> 00:04:09.533
but I have daily

00:04:09.533 --> 00:04:11.000
needs such as sunscreen,

00:04:11.000 --> 00:04:14.033
cleansing, moisturizing, repairing, etc.

00:04:14.066 --> 00:04:15.033
Paula's Choice

00:04:15.033 --> 00:04:18.433
also has several series to meet this demand stage

00:04:18.433 --> 00:04:19.000
. It

00:04:19.000 --> 00:04:22.466
mainly includes the three series of Clear, Calm and Defense.

00:04:22.466 --> 00:04:24.466
In between these two needs, there

00:04:24.466 --> 00:04:25.933
is another category

00:04:25.933 --> 00:04:28.333
, that is, I have certain effectiveness needs.

00:04:28.333 --> 00:04:30.266
My skin has begun to have spots and

00:04:30.266 --> 00:04:31.833
is starting to age a little,

00:04:31.833 --> 00:04:34.633
but it has not reached the level of pathological intensity.

00:04:34.633 --> 00:04:38.300
This is the effectiveness demand section.

00:04:38.300 --> 00:04:40.833
Paula's Choice also corresponds to two series,

00:04:40.833 --> 00:04:42.466
one is resist

00:04:42.466 --> 00:04:44.133
and the other is exfoliant.

00:04:44.266 --> 00:04:45.433
In addition, there

00:04:45.433 --> 00:04:48.000
is a series that transcends all these needs

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:49.666
called earth. Source

00:04:49.733 --> 00:04:51.833
stands for Earth Resources series.

00:04:51.833 --> 00:04:53.500
This is a series that

00:04:53.500 --> 00:04:55.233
focuses on natural and pure skin care

00:04:55.233 --> 00:04:56.666
, going beyond the need for efficacy.

00:04:57.133 --> 00:04:58.833
People who have used Paula's Choice

00:04:58.833 --> 00:05:01.000
may have a little problem

00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:03.433
. The Paula's Choice series products

00:05:03.433 --> 00:05:04.433
are colorful and

00:05:04.433 --> 00:05:05.933
there are many colors.

00:05:05.933 --> 00:05:07.500
People may naturally think

00:05:07.500 --> 00:05:08.933
that different colors

00:05:08.933 --> 00:05:11.200
represent different product series.

00:05:11.200 --> 00:05:12.500
But in fact,

00:05:12.500 --> 00:05:13.633
it is not the color,

00:05:13.633 --> 00:05:16.466
but the main ingredient.

00:05:16.466 --> 00:05:18.866
If you look closely at the Paula's Choice website,

00:05:18.866 --> 00:05:20.633
there is a column called

00:05:20.633 --> 00:05:23.100
Ingredients Dictionary.

00:05:23.100 --> 00:05:25.400
There is a chart in it

00:05:25.400 --> 00:05:28.400
. The different colors represent

00:05:28.400 --> 00:05:30.466
different ingredients

00:05:30.466 --> 00:05:31.533
and their corresponding

00:05:31.533 --> 00:05:32.333
effects .

00:05:32.333 --> 00:05:33.066
For example

00:05:33.066 --> 00:05:34.700
, the retinol series

00:05:34.700 --> 00:05:36.033
is purple

00:05:36.033 --> 00:05:38.700
and is more suitable for wrinkles and acne.

00:05:38.700 --> 00:05:40.666
Various products containing retinol are

00:05:40.666 --> 00:05:41.866
also in purple bottles.

00:05:41.866 --> 00:05:43.733
VC corresponds to orange, and

00:05:43.733 --> 00:05:46.233
the essence containing VC is in orange bottles. Now that I

00:05:48.833 --> 00:05:49.933
have explained how to classify,

00:05:49.933 --> 00:05:52.700
I will tell you what everyone is most concerned about:

00:05:52.700 --> 00:05:54.900
how to choose Paula's Choice products.

00:05:54.900 --> 00:05:57.266
Let's start with the first series, clinical

00:05:57.266 --> 00:05:58.033
Clinical

00:05:58.033 --> 00:05:59.866
means

00:05:59.866 --> 00:06:00.666
clinical. As the name suggests,

00:06:00.666 --> 00:06:04.066
this series of products contains

00:06:04.066 --> 00:06:06.533
ingredients with relatively high concentrations, and they

00:06:06.533 --> 00:06:07.800
are used more vigorously

00:06:07.800 --> 00:06:09.066
, more abundantly,

00:06:09.066 --> 00:06:11.033
and more comprehensively.

00:06:11.033 --> 00:06:12.000
Simply put,

00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:14.200
this product series is here to solve your problems.

00:06:14.200 --> 00:06:15.700
If you don't have a serious problem,

00:06:15.700 --> 00:06:17.900
you won't need it.

00:06:17.900 --> 00:06:19.833
This series is often praised by fans

00:06:19.833 --> 00:06:23.600
as a collection of Paula's Choice crazy an alcohols.

00:06:23.600 --> 00:06:26.666
For example, the three products in the clinical series

00:06:26.666 --> 00:06:28.666
are all an alcohol products

00:06:28.666 --> 00:06:29.666
, but their formula

00:06:29.666 --> 00:06:31.866
logic and applicable groups are completely different.

00:06:31.866 --> 00:06:34.500
I call this one ordinary double an.

00:06:34.500 --> 00:06:37.833
Its main ingredients are 0.3% an

00:06:37.833 --> 00:06:40.266
alcohol and 2% bakuchiol.

00:06:40.266 --> 00:06:41.266
Bakuchiol

00:06:41.266 --> 00:06:43.100
is a plant-based product

00:06:43.100 --> 00:06:45.200
and has the same an alcohol effect.

00:06:45.200 --> 00:06:47.066
This can promote the production of collagen and other

00:06:47.066 --> 00:06:49.633
similar effects of plant-derived retinol.

00:06:49.700 --> 00:06:52.100
After the two retinols in this product are combined, it

00:06:52.100 --> 00:06:54.400
is obvious that it is used to treat wrinkles

00:06:54.400 --> 00:06:56.400
, increase collagen content

00:06:56.400 --> 00:06:57.633
, and fight aging.

00:06:57.833 --> 00:06:58.800
In short

00:06:58.800 --> 00:07:00.866
, if you have wrinkle problems,

00:07:00.866 --> 00:07:02.333
decreased elasticity,

00:07:02.333 --> 00:07:03.533
and sagging face problems,

00:07:03.533 --> 00:07:05.933
you can choose this ordinary double a

00:07:06.000 --> 00:07:07.266
. The formula of this next one

00:07:07.266 --> 00:07:09.833
is different from the previous one.

00:07:09.833 --> 00:07:11.600
It is 3%

00:07:11.600 --> 00:07:12.733
tranexamic acid

00:07:12.733 --> 00:07:18.000
plus 0.5% bakuchiol and 5% niacinamide.

00:07:18.100 --> 00:07:20.033
So when you look at this one, you can see that

00:07:20.033 --> 00:07:21.433
tranexamic acid and niacinamide

00:07:21.433 --> 00:07:24.400
are the good ingredients

00:07:24.400 --> 00:07:25.866
we talked about in the whitening issue.

00:07:25.866 --> 00:07:28.700
Add 0.5% bakuchiol

00:07:28.700 --> 00:07:31.300
, which is a plant retinol with an anti-aging effect.

00:07:31.300 --> 00:07:32.333
So it is obvious that

00:07:32.333 --> 00:07:33.533
this one is used to treat

00:07:33.533 --> 00:07:35.933
uneven skin tone , dark spots, and dull skin problems

00:07:35.933 --> 00:07:38.133
caused by aging.

00:07:38.133 --> 00:07:38.800
The next one

00:07:38.800 --> 00:07:40.933
I call Pro Double A

00:07:40.933 --> 00:07:46.533
is 0.1% a plus 0.16 adapalene

00:07:46.666 --> 00:07:47.866
alpha aldehyde. We know

00:07:47.866 --> 00:07:51.300
that it is a VA family ingredient that

00:07:51.300 --> 00:07:52.800
is closer to alpha acid than retinol.

00:07:52.800 --> 00:07:54.900
Its metabolism The path is shorter

00:07:54.900 --> 00:07:56.000
and the onset is faster,

00:07:56.000 --> 00:07:57.133
while Adapalene

00:07:57.133 --> 00:07:59.066
is a derivative of alpha acid,

00:07:59.133 --> 00:08:00.333
so this one

00:08:00.333 --> 00:08:03.266
is basically

00:08:03.266 --> 00:08:05.233
an ingredient of the alpha alcohol family

00:08:05.233 --> 00:08:06.933
that is very close to alpha acid. It is suitable for people

00:08:06.933 --> 00:08:09.133
who have aged rapidly,

00:08:09.133 --> 00:08:10.333
their face has sagged,

00:08:10.333 --> 00:08:12.700
their pores are very large

00:08:12.700 --> 00:08:15.833
, and
they have obvious aging-type pores.

00:08:15.833 --> 00:08:17.633
In summary, if you are just ordinary and want to fight wrinkles

00:08:17.633 --> 00:08:18.633
and improve skin elasticity,

00:08:18.666 --> 00:08:21.133
such anti-aging problems,

00:08:21.133 --> 00:08:22.866
use

00:08:22.866 --> 00:08:24.233
this ordinary double a.

00:08:24.233 --> 00:08:25.800
If you want to change the dullness

00:08:25.800 --> 00:08:28.800
and uneven color

00:08:28.800 --> 00:08:30.133
of the skin caused by aging,

00:08:30.133 --> 00:08:31.800
use this color-correcting lip a.

00:08:31.800 --> 00:08:34.100
If you want to target

00:08:34.100 --> 00:08:36.466
more difficult aging problems such as large pores,

00:08:36.466 --> 00:08:37.800
use this Pro double a

00:08:37.800 --> 00:08:39.633
. For skin color problems,

00:08:39.633 --> 00:08:42.433
there is another product in the clinical series that is worth mentioning,

00:08:42.433 --> 00:08:46.033
which is this 25% VC essence.

00:08:46.033 --> 00:08:47.300
It can basically be said

00:08:47.300 --> 00:08:50.833
to challenge the solubility limit of VC.

00:08:50.833 --> 00:08:52.466
The highest concentration you can add

00:08:52.466 --> 00:08:53.700
has been added.

00:08:53.700 --> 00:08:56.066
Although

00:08:56.066 --> 00:08:58.266
the antioxidant effect of such a high concentration of VC is unquestionable

00:08:58.266 --> 00:09:00.066
, it is especially

00:09:00.066 --> 00:09:01.800
for Asians .

00:09:01.800 --> 00:09:03.700
This concentration is a bit high

00:09:03.700 --> 00:09:04.933
for East Asians

00:09:04.933 --> 00:09:07.466
because East Asians

00:09:07.466 --> 00:09:08.666
actually

00:09:08.666 --> 00:09:09.900
have limited ability

00:09:09.900 --> 00:09:12.133
and speed to absorb VC. It can easily accumulate in the stratum corneum

00:09:12.133 --> 00:09:13.200
and then be absorbed slowly.

00:09:13.200 --> 00:09:15.133
When you use such a high concentration,

00:09:15.133 --> 00:09:17.000
it can easily yellow the stratum corneum.

00:09:17.000 --> 00:09:17.900
So

00:09:17.900 --> 00:09:19.333
although this concentration is very high

00:09:19.333 --> 00:09:20.333
and effective

00:09:20.333 --> 00:09:22.666
, I do not recommend it for East Asians.

00:09:22.666 --> 00:09:24.133
In addition, the clinical series

00:09:24.133 --> 00:09:24.833
has a pair

00:09:24.833 --> 00:09:27.966
of combinations that seem a bit schizophrenic.

00:09:27.966 --> 00:09:31.700
It uses a 1% high-concentration

00:09:31.700 --> 00:09:35.200
retinol and a ceramide cream to match

00:09:35.200 --> 00:09:36.133
. It feels

00:09:36.133 --> 00:09:37.066
like

00:09:37.066 --> 00:09:37.800
retinol

00:09:37.800 --> 00:09:39.600
can promote keratin metabolism

00:09:39.600 --> 00:09:40.533
and control oil

00:09:40.533 --> 00:09:43.600
, which can easily turn oily skin into dry skin and

00:09:43.600 --> 00:09:44.866
cause breakouts.

00:09:44.933 --> 00:09:46.233
If she is afraid that you will break out,

00:09:46.233 --> 00:09:48.933
she will give you a ceramide moisturizing cream

00:09:48.933 --> 00:09:49.833
to moisturize you,

00:09:49.833 --> 00:09:51.266
so that you won't break out.

00:09:51.266 --> 00:09:52.700
So this idea

00:09:52.700 --> 00:09:54.400
seems a bit schizophrenic,

00:09:54.400 --> 00:09:55.600
a bit like taking off clothes

00:09:55.600 --> 00:09:57.066
and putting on clothes at the same time.

00:09:57.066 --> 00:09:59.600
But if you are dealing with aging problems

00:09:59.600 --> 00:10:00.633
and wrinkles,

00:10:00.633 --> 00:10:02.833
this pair of combinations is It's very suitable

00:10:02.833 --> 00:10:06.133
because it retains the functions of retinol such as boosting collagen,

00:10:06.133 --> 00:10:07.000
tightening the skin, and

00:10:07.000 --> 00:10:09.800
improving skin elasticity

00:10:09.800 --> 00:10:11.633
, and it also avoids its side effects.

00:10:11.633 --> 00:10:14.666
However, if you use retinol for,

00:10:14.666 --> 00:10:15.833
for example, anti-acne

00:10:15.833 --> 00:10:17.800
and oil control,

00:10:17.800 --> 00:10:19.800
this combination is not suitable.

00:10:19.800 --> 00:10:21.066
The Clinical series

00:10:21.066 --> 00:10:24.700
also has a product with 20% niacinamide.

00:10:24.700 --> 00:10:25.633
I don't recommend

00:10:25.633 --> 00:10:27.233
this product

00:10:27.233 --> 00:10:27.833
to East Asians

00:10:27.833 --> 00:10:30.100
because its concentration is a bit too high.

00:10:30.100 --> 00:10:31.600
If you use it for whitening,

00:10:31.600 --> 00:10:35.000
5% to 10% is a safe range for East Asians.

00:10:35.000 --> 00:10:36.700
If you use it for oil control,

00:10:36.700 --> 00:10:38.733
10% is basically the limit.

00:10:38.733 --> 00:10:40.133
If you use more,

00:10:40.133 --> 00:10:41.500
your skin will become dry and cracked.

